O-O 9. Be3 Qc7 10. g4 Re8
{ Black is preparing to play ...Bf8 in order to guard her kingside. } 11. f5
{ White prepares to open the position with fxe6.   11.g5  is also dangerous.  11...Nfd7  12.Bh5  g6  13.Bg4  Judit played this against Hans Ree, and won a nice minituare after  13...Nc6 ??  14.Nxe6  fxe6  15.Bxe6+  but Black could have played better on move 13 with 13... Bf8. }
11... Bf8
{ 11...exf5  is not a natural move  (...exf5 weakens the d5-square)  but Black can get into some serious trouble if he doesn't play this move due to White's ability to take on e6.  12.Nxf5  Bxf5  13.Rxf5  White's position is much better due to his bishop pair and lead in development, but Black isn't lost yet.   11...h6  Black defends against g5  as 12. h4 is well met by 12... d5 ! and Black threatens ...Qg3+. White still has the more pleasant position and can fight for the win with  12.fxe6  followed by Qd3 or g5. }
12. g5 Nfd7 13. Nxe6
{ White sacrifices a piece to open the position. 13. Nxe6 is stronger than 13. fxe6 because after 13. Nxe6 White is able to play fxg6 in response to ...g6. }
13... fxe6 14. Bh5
{ Black's queenside is undeveloped, White has a tremendous attack for the sacrificed knight. }
14... g6
{ Black is essentially forced to give some material back with this move in order to prevent fxe6.   14...Re7  15.fxe6  15...Nb6  16.Qf3  16...Qd8  17.Bxb6  17...Qxb6+  18.Rf2  Qd8  19.Raf1   14...Rd8  15.fxe6  15...Nb6  16.Bf7+  Kh8  17.Qh5 }
15. fxg6 Re7
{ 15...hxg6  16.Bxg6  Re7  17.Qh5  17...Ne5  White would win with Rf7 if Black did not play this move.  18.Rxf8+  Kxf8  19.Qh8# }
16. Nd5
{ This theme keeps coming up: White has a huge lead in development and sacrifices material to weaken Black's defenses. Quite often, a second sacrifice comes to shatter the remains. }
16... exd5 17. Qxd5+ Kh8
{ Black's king is very weak and Black's queenside is still undeveloped. } 18.
gxh7 Rxh7 { 18...Rg7  19.Bd4   18...Kxh7  19.g6+  Kh8  20.Bg4 } 19. Bg6
{ 19.g6  also wins for White. } 19... Bg7
{ Black gives back some material in an attempt to finish her development. } 20.
Bxh7 Qd8 { 20...Kxh7  21.g6+ } 21. Bf5 Ne5 22. Qd1
{ White has won the sacrificed material back and has a decisive initiative. }
22... Bxf5 23. exf5 Qe8 24. g6 Ng4 25. Bd4 Qe4 26. f6 Nc6 27. fxg7+ Kg8 28.
Rf8+ Rxf8 29. gxf8=Q+ Kxf8 30. Qf1+ *

